"&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nRMP 06&#xa0;&#xa0;Written evidence submitted by Save Our Royal Mail Campaign&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nExecutive Summary&#xa0;\nUniversal service obligations\n&#xa0;\nPrices\n&#xa0;\nLocal Post Offices\n&#xa0;\nHeritage\n&#xa0;\nRemaining successful in the public sector\n&#xa0;Save Our Royal Mail&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nRoyal Mail Privatisation and the threat to postal services&#xa0;\n“\nFor the longer term, the universal service is just impractical\n…\nI would suggest in 3-5 years there will be only three maximum deliveries per week and that will be more than e\nnough because most of what’s delivered now more and more is what’s called junk mail\n.”\nAs someone who knows more about postal economics than most, Mr Senior was even more \ndownbeat about \nthe long term future\n of the USO\n:\n“Within \n15 years there will be no Roya\nl Mail or no traditional letters service at all.”\nAlong with postal academics, many businesses leaders in the carrier sector are equally convinced that the universal postal service will change fundamentally. \nJames Greenbury, Chief Executive of carrier \nParcel2Go said recently that the six day delivery will be outdated and redundant in ten years time.\n Mr Greenbury also suggests the privatisation will herald an era of price rises as well.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Royal Mail privatisation and the threat to the post office network&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Royal Mail privatisation and the threat to prices&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Privatisation and the threat to Royal Mail’s heritage&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nThe better alternative to privatisation&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nConclusion&#xa0;\n&#xa0;30\n August 2013\n&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n Sample Size: 1779 GB Adults. Fieldwork: 8\nth\n-9\nth\n -July \n2013\n. \nhttp://yougov.co.uk/news/2013/07/11/two-thirds-public-oppose-royal-mail-sell/\n \nBBC \nRadio Five\n Live\n interview\n \n5\nth\n July 2013\n. \nhttp://saveourroyalmail.org/2013/05/government-postal-guarantees-not-worth-the-paper-they-are-written-on/\n \nhttp://www.prweb.com/releases/2013/7/prweb10951512.htm\n \nhttp://www.saga.co.uk/newsroom/press-releases/2012/november/stamps.aspx\n"